properties.areaDesc: Southern Inner Channels; Dixon Entrance to Cape Decision Coastal Area
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 29 at 5:36AM AKST until January 30 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 70 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Portions of the southern Inner Channels and the
southeast Gulf Coast including Ketchikan, Craig, Hydaburg, and
Metlakatla.

* WHEN...From late tonight through Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds may be lower should storm's take it farther
north.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
